  "text": "The global shared-layer blending (GSLB) method was first introduced in [CITATION_1] ; it was developed to predict the layer shape of the tapered composite structure according to its thickness distribution. However, the GSLB method can only be applied to the same ply orientation. Thus, assume that all layers have the same ply orientation in minimum-thickness distribution (Table 3) , the GSLB is applied to obtain the shape of the shared layers, in which the constraints CT1 and CT12 are enforced. The detailed description of GSLB is provided in [CITATION_2] , here, the summarised algorithm is given in Algorithm 3. The shared layer covers all panels is defined as the global shared layer; on the contrary, the layer not covers all panels is defined as the subregion shared layer [CITATION_3] . the minimum number of all panels. All panels that contain the ply orientation minus the minimum number, the set of panels contain the minimum number of ply orientation assemble the shared layer.",
